snippet: By one measure, stocks are on an almost incredibly long winning streak, yet many investors have hardly noticed.
abstract: Jeff Sommer Strategies column observes that although stocks are on a long winning streak, long slog back toward the level of more than a decade ago has disillusioned many people; says even if stocks keep grinding upward, it may be awhile before there is much excitement about the market.
lead_paragraph: By one measure, stocks are on an almost incredibly long winning streak, yet many investors have hardly noticed.

headline.print_headline: This Ironman Market Is Still Lacking Respect
headline.main: This Ironman Market Is Still Lacking Respect
